@type MonoSpec
@kind struct
@fields
  generic_name: str — Original generic function/type name
  specialized_name: str — Monomorphized name (e.g., "identity_i64")
  type_arg_0: i64 — First type argument ID
  type_arg_1: i64 — Second type argument ID
  type_arg_2: i64 — Third type argument ID
@purpose Records a monomorphization specialization, mapping a generic function/type to its concrete instantiation. Used by codegen to emit specialized versions of generic code.
@invariants specialized_name follows the pattern "basename_typesuffix0_typesuffix1". Sentinel has generic_name="" and specialized_name="".
@notes Type arguments are capped at 3, matching the generic parameter limit. [src: types.aria:601]
@source_file src/checker/types.aria
@source_line 601

---

@type TypeRegistry
@kind struct
@fields
  struct_defs: [StructDef] — All struct/sum type definitions (1-based)
  fn_sigs: [FnSig] — All function signatures (1-based)
  mono_specs: [MonoSpec] — Monomorphization records (1-based)
  deprecated_names: [str] — Deprecated symbol names (1-based)
  deprecated_msgs: [str] — Deprecation messages (parallel to deprecated_names)
  cold_names: [str] — Cold-path function names (1-based)
@purpose Central registry for all type and function definitions discovered during checking. Provides lookup-by-name for structs, functions, monomorphization specs, and annotation metadata. Passed through to codegen as part of CheckResult.
@invariants All arrays are 1-based with sentinels at index 0. deprecated_names and deprecated_msgs are parallel arrays. Struct type IDs >= TY_STRUCT_BASE map to struct_defs via: index = type_id - TY_STRUCT_BASE + 1.
@antipatterns Linear search is used for all lookups (reg_find_struct, reg_find_fn, etc.); adequate for compiler-sized programs but would not scale to very large registries.
@source_file src/checker/types.aria
@source_line 614

