@type Checker
@kind struct
@fields
  tokens: [Token] — Token stream from lexer
  pos: i64 — Current token position
  store: TypeStore — Type store (grows as new types are encountered)
  registry: TypeRegistry — Type/function registry
  treg: TraitRegistry — Trait registry
  diagnostics: DiagnosticBag — Accumulated diagnostics (errors and warnings)
  table: SymbolTable — Symbol table from resolver (used for mutability checks)
  current_scope: i64 — Active scope ID
  file: str — Source file path (for diagnostic spans)
  pool: NodePool — AST node pool from parser
  env_names: [str] — Type environment variable names (parallel array, 1-based)
  env_types: [i64] — Type environment variable type IDs (parallel array)
  env_scopes: [i64] — Type environment variable scope IDs (parallel array)
  fn_return_type: i64 — Current function's declared return type
  fn_error_type: i64 — Current function's declared error type (0 = infallible)
  fn_current_name: str — Current function name (for effect checking and Self resolution)
  in_loop: bool — Whether currently inside a loop (for break/continue validation)
@purpose Immutable state object threaded through all checking functions. Every mutation creates a new Checker via _cset_* helper functions. This functional-update pattern avoids mutable state issues and works within bootstrap compiler constraints.
@invariants env_names, env_types, and env_scopes are parallel arrays. fn_return_type/fn_error_type are set per-function via _cset_fn_ctx. fn_current_name is "_entry" for entry blocks and "_test" for test blocks (these bypass effect checking).
@notes The _cset_* helpers (_cset_pos, _cset_store, _cset_reg, _cset_diag, _cset_fn_ctx, _cset_treg, _cset_loop) each create a full copy of the Checker with one field changed. This is verbose but necessary because the bootstrap compiler cannot generate struct-update syntax. [src: checker.aria:97-144]
@source_file src/checker/checker.aria
@source_line 18

