@const TY_STRUCT_BASE
@value_type i64
@value 10000
@purpose Offset for registry-based struct type IDs. Type IDs >= TY_STRUCT_BASE index into TypeRegistry.struct_defs via: index = type_id - TY_STRUCT_BASE + 1. This separates the TypeStore ID space from the registry's struct definition space.
@notes User-defined types in the TypeStore start at index 21, but their struct definitions in the registry use IDs starting at 10000+. The two ID spaces serve different purposes: TypeStore IDs for type checking, struct_defs indices for field/variant access.
