@fn check
@sig (tokens: [Token], index: DeclIndex, pool: NodePool, table: SymbolTable, file: str) -> CheckResult
@calls [new_store, new_registry, new_trait_registry, populate_builtins, _pass1_types, _pass2_fns, _pass3_bodies]
@purpose Main entry point for the type checker. Runs three sequential passes over the DeclIndex: (1) register all type/enum declarations, (2) register all function signatures, trait declarations, and constants, (3) check all function/impl/entry/test bodies for type correctness. Returns the complete CheckResult for downstream compilation stages.
@pre tokens must be the complete token stream. index must be a valid DeclIndex from the resolver. pool must contain AST nodes from the parser. table must be the resolved SymbolTable.
@post CheckResult.diagnostics contains all type errors and warnings. CheckResult.store/registry/treg contain the full type information for codegen.
@effects Accumulates diagnostics. Registers monomorphization specializations on-demand during pass 3.
@workflow Called from the compiler's main pipeline after lexing, parsing, and resolution. Its output (CheckResult) feeds into the lowerer and codegen.
@notes The three-pass architecture ensures forward references work: a function can reference a type declared later in the file (registered in pass 1) and call a function declared later (registered in pass 2). Generic function bodies are skipped in pass 3 and checked per-specialization when monomorphization is triggered by a call site. Effect violations use per-effect warning codes E0300 (Io), E0301 (Fs), E0302 (Net), E0303 (Ffi), E0304 (Async) for both user-declared and builtin function calls. [src: checker.aria:3107-3160]
@source_file src/checker/checker.aria
@source_line 4057
